docs.abstract: A series of Trump family lawsuits to block House subpoenas has left Democrats steaming, and again talking about impeaching the president for obstruction of justice.
docs.snippet: A series of Trump family lawsuits to block House subpoenas has left Democrats steaming, and again talking about impeaching the president for obstruction of justice.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump family lawsuit to block oversight of its finances has House Democrats scrambling to confront what many see as the gravest threat to congressional independence since the Nixon era, reviving internal debate over the ultimate weapon in the Democrats’ arsenal: impeachment.

headline.main: As Trump Family Sues to Block Subpoenas, Democrats Ponder Impeachment

docs.abstract: Carl Kline’s appearance before Congress was the latest episode in a continuing debate over the vetting and approval of the people working for President Trump.
docs.snippet: Carl Kline’s appearance before Congress was the latest episode in a continuing debate over the vetting and approval of the people working for President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Carl Kline, the former director of the White House’s Personnel Security Office, told the House Oversight and Reform Committee this week that he had overruled the recommendations of his staff and approved security clearances for White House officials on his own authority, and denied that President Trump or anyone else had directed him to do it.

headline.main: Ex-White House Official Says No One Pressured Him to Overturn Security Clearance Recommendations
headline.print_headline: No Pressure to Approve Staff,  Ex-White House Official Says
